data.title: Taylor Swift Confirms Song Lyric Is A Philadelphia Reference
data.meta_description: On her first night of residency in Philadelphia Taylor Swift confirms that she references the Eagles football team in one of her songs.
data.text:
Taylor Swift confirms song lyric is a Philadelphia Eagles reference.

On her first night of residency at Lincoln Financial Field in Philadelphia (5/12/23) Taylor Swift confirmed that she references the Eagles football team in one of her songs.

She sang ‘Gold Rush’ as one of her secret songs for the first night of three shows in Philadelphia. During her intro she mentioned how she saw fans online wondering if she references the band the Eagles or if she is tipping her hat at the Philadelphia Eagles football team.

Turns out it is a nod to her hometown football team, Philadelphia Eagles.

I see me padding across your wooden floors

With my Eagles T-shirt hanging from the door

Swift is from Reading and said at the beginning of the show that she grew up watching her dad watch the Eagles on television.

Taylor Swift continues her three night Philadelphia residency tonight (5/13).
